ranya-dari-jakarta|title=Ada Tambahan 17 Pasien Corona Baru, 14 di Antaranya dari Jakarta|last=Luxiana|first=Kadek Melda|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n** Indonesia announced that it will start to quarantine non symptomatic COVID-19 patients on their own home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4941325/kemenkes-sekarang-pasien-positif-corona-bisa-diisolasi-mandiri-di-rumah|title=Kemenkes: Sekarang Pasien Positif Corona Bisa Diisolasi Mandiri di Rumah|last=Melda|first=Kadek|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n* March 17 - The Indonesian Government announced another 38 new cases of COVID-19, bringing the total number to 172.<ref>{{citeweb|title=Data Terbaru Virus Corona: Total Kasus Positif Melonjak Jadi 172|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942786/data-terbaru-virus-corona-total-kasus-positif-melonjak-jadi-172|publisher=Detik|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n* March 18 \n** Coronavirus cases rises to 227.<ref>{{citeweb|title=Update Terbaru: Jumlah Pasien Positif Corona Capai 227 Orang|url=https://nasional.tempo.co/read/1321108/update-terbaru-jumlah-pasien-positif-corona-capai-227-orang|publisher=Tempo|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n** West Kalimantan declares an emergency due to the ongoing COVID-19 outbreak<ref>{{citeweb|title=Ada 2 Kasus Positif, Gubernur Tetapkan Kalbar KLB Corona|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944658/ada-2-kasus-positif-gubernur-tetapkan-kalbar-klb-corona|publisher=Detik|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n* March 19\n** The government announced 81 new cases of COVID-19, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 308 in the country. It also announced that rapid testing tools for the virus would be ordered from China.<ref>{{citeweb|title=Pemerintah Meralat: Kasus Positif Corona di RI Jadi 308 Kasus|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200319182124-4-146252/pemerintah-meralat-kasus-positif-corona-di-ri-jadi-308-kasus|publisher=CNBC Indonesia|accessdat